Turkey's%20S-400s%20have%20been%20put%20into%20operation.%20In%20November%202022%2C%20then-Defense%20Minister%20Hulusi%20Akar%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hurriyetdailynews.com%2Fs-400-air-defense-system-ready-for-use-if-needed-defense-minister-178753%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Ankara%20has%20%26quot%3Bno%20problems%20with%20the%20S-400%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20system%20%26quot%3Bis%20in%20place%20and%20ready%20for%20use.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIts%20purported%20upcoming%20deployment%20on%20the%20Iraqi%20border%20would%20be%20the%20first%20time%20Turkish%20S-400s%20have%20been%20put%20into%20use%20five%20years%20after%20Ankara%20received%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAli%20Bakir%2C%20a%20Turkey%20expert%20at%20Qatar%20University's%20Ibn%20Khaldon%20Center%20and%20nonresident%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Atlantic%20Council's%20Scowcroft%20Middle%20East%20Security%20Initiative%2C%20is%20skeptical%20of%20the%20report%20but%20doesn't%20outright%20dismiss%20the%20possibility.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThis%20could%20be%20a%20trial%20balloon%2C%20an%20operational%20requirement%20due%20to%20the%20foreign%20threat%20in%20Northern%20Iraq%2C%20where%20Turkish%20troops%20are%20stationed%2C%20or%20simply%20untrue%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20Bakir%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20S-400%20is%20deployed%20for%20operational%20needs%2C%20it%20could%20be%20to%20counter%20the%20potential%20threat%20of%20Iran's%20ballistic%20missiles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20Turkey's%20other%20air%20defenses%20are%20capable%20of%20combating%20aerial%20threats%20from%20the%20PKK%2C%20Turkey%20requires%20an%20advanced%20system%20for%20intercepting%20ballistic%20missiles%20fired%20from%20Iran.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BConsidering%20that%20Ankara%20has%20stationed%20troops%20in%20Northern%20Iraq%2C%20it%20would%20be%20more%20logical%20to%20deploy%20such%20a%20system%20to%20protect%20them%20during%20regional%20escalation%20or%20confrontation%2C%26quot%3B%20Bakir%20said.%20%26quot%3BIran%20has%20used%20missiles%20lately%20against%20Northern%20Iraq.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBakir%20said%20that%20the%20recent%20missile%20attacks%20between%20Israel%20and%20Iran%20may%20be%20a%20further%20rationale%20to%20deploy%20the%20S-400%20in%20Turkey's%20east.%26quot%3BSuch%20deployment%20will%20serve%20Turkey's%20security%20as%20well%20as%20the%20security%20of%20Iraq%2C%20which%20is%20improving%20its%20ties%20with%20Ankara%20lately%20in%20an%20unprecedented%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Bakir%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDeploying%20S-400s%20as%20a%20contingency%20to%20counter%20Iranian%20missiles%20could%20create%20%26quot%3Ban%20extremely%20complex%20situation%26quot%3B%20for%20Turkey%2C%20said%20Suleyman%20Ozeren%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20the%20American%20University%20and%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Orion%20Policy%20Institute.%26quot%3BSuch%20a%20move%20might%20mean%20that%20Turkey%20would%20be%20using%20the%20Russian%20weapon%20system%20against%20Russia's%20most%20loyal%20ally%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%26quot%3B%20Ozeren%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20Turkey%20may%20use%20the%20potential%20threat%20of%20Iran-linked%20militia%20groups%20or%20PKK%20as%20a%20pretext%20to%20deploy%20S-400s.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20predicts%20a%20deployment%20would%20serve%20three%20primary%20objectives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20the%20S-400s%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20yet%20least%20productive%20policy%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20Ozeren%20said.%20%26quot%3BBy%20deploying%20them%20and%20making%20a%20lot%20of%20noise%20about%20it%2C%20the%20AKP%20may%20aim%20to%20silence%20critics%20at%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20AKP%20is%20President%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan's%20party%2C%20which%20decided%20to%20buy%20the%20S-400%20in%20the%20late%202010s%20and%20has%20defended%20the%20contentious%20purchase%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BSecond%2C%20Ankara%20may%20want%20to%20prove%20to%20Moscow%20that%20its%20military%20cooperation%20still%20stands%2C%26quot%3B%20Ozeren%20said.%20%26quot%3BThird%2C%20such%20a%20decision%20may%20aim%20to%20send%20a%20message%20to%20the%20West%20%E2%80%94%20primarily%20to%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20that%20Ankara's%20position%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Russia%20and%20NATO%20remains%20unchanged.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20noted%20the%20Turkish%20S-400%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bstandalone%20system%26quot%3B%20incompatible%20with%20NATO%20systems%2C%20limiting%20its%20use%20and%20confirming%20its%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20cost%20and%20lack%20of%20functionality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Turkish%20deployment%20could%20escalate%20the%20lingering%20dispute%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%2C%20then-Acting%20Deputy%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Victoria%20Nuland%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-01-30%2Fus-ready-to-reopen-turkey-f-35-talks-if-russian-s-400-system-issue-resolved%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Washington%20could%20discuss%20readmitting%20Ankara%20into%20the%20F-35%20program%20if%20it%20resolves%20the%20S-400%20issue.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20not%20about%20where%20Ankara%20deploys%20S-400s%20but%20about%20the%20S-400%20remaining%20in%20Turkey's%20possession%2C%26quot%3B%20Ozeren%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBakir%20argued%20that%20weapons%20are%20purchased%20%26quot%3Bwith%20the%20intention%20of%20use%26quot%3B%20for%20either%20%26quot%3Boffensive%20or%20defensive%20